ta><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BHXW.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>BHX2</code><airport>BHX</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>PURPLE PARKING PARK AND RIDE</name><description>&lt;li&gt;BRAND NEW!&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Exclusive.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Only 15 minutes away from the Airport&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Transfers run 24 hours a day.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;BRAND NEW!&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Exclusive&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;24 hour transfers included&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;15 mins transfer&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Faraday Ave, Hams Hall Distribution Centre, Coleshill, Birmingham, B46 1AL</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; IF YOU ARE USING A SAT NAV: Enter the following postcode - B46 1AL or Location: Lea Marston Faraday Ave. DO NOT SELECT FARADAY AVE, QUINTON.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From North West: Follow the M6 South and exit at Junction 4a.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs for the M42 North.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; As you join the M42 remain in the nearside lane &amp;amp; exit the motorway at Junction 9.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs for the A446 Coleshill and Coventry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout (Hams Hall Roundabout) turn left into Hams Hall.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Go to the next roundabout and turn left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Purple Parking / APH&amp;nbsp; is on the right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the South via the M5 or Wales: Follow the M5 North and join M42 North at Junction 4A.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the M42 and exit at Junction 9.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs for the A446 Coleshill and Coventry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout (Hams Hall Roundabout) turn left into Hams Hall.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Go to the next roundabout and turn left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Purple Parking/APH&amp;nbsp; is on the right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival please report to Reception and present your confirmation slip or quote your booking reference number.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full instructions for return procedures will be issued on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>01675 465916</helpline><distanceToAirport>Conveniently located just off the M42 Junction 9.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Purple Parking operate transfers to and from the airport on demand, 24 hours a day which take 10 - 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>15 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park has barrier control, CCTV and holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>&lt;p&gt; Additional charges may be payable on collection for oversized vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>This service is ideal for disabled travellers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BHX2.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"BOH\"><name>Bournemouth Airport</name><shortname>bournemouthairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks/></airport><airport code=\"BRS\"><name>Bristol International Airport</name><shortname>bristolinternationalairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>BRSH</code><airport>BRS</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>BRISTOL AIRPORT LONG STAY</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure on-site parking at Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Self-parking - no need to hand over your keys.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;On-site parking at Bristol Airport&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Self Parking&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keep your keys with you&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Minimum stay 1 day&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bristol Airport, Bristol, BS48 3DY</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;This car park uses Automatic Number Plate Recognition (ANPR). Please ensure that your booking confirmation includes the correct vehicle registration number.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 North: Exit the M5 at Junction 18.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A4 towards Bristol and the airport for about 5 miles.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right onto the A38 and follow it to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The long stay car park is located on the right as you enter the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 South: Exit the M5 at Junction 22.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A38 towards Weston Super Mare.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A38 for approximately 17 miles to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The long stay car park is located on the right as you enter the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>At the entry barrier, the ANPR camera will read your vehicle registration plate and apply the booking. Please take a ticket from the barrier column and proceed to find a space in the car park, retaining the ticket that you have been issued.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>At the exit barrier, insert the same ticket issued on your arrival. The barrier will rise automatically for you to exit the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0871 334 4450</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located at the airport.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Bristol Airport Long Stay operate transfers to and from the airport terminal every 20 minutes which take just 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>All of Bristol Airport's on-site car parks are well lit with security fencing, CCTV, automatic number plate registration and 24 hour staffing. They also hold the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has special assistance bays for Blue Badge holders and help buttons to call for assistance at the barriers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BRSH.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>BRSI</code><airport>BRS</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>BRISTOL AIRPORT MEET AND GREET</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Your car is collected and returned to you at the Express Drop-Off and Pick-Up car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Ultimate convenience in Bristol Airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Collected and returned to airport terminal&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;A safe and convenient parking solution&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bristol International Airport, Bristol, BS48 3DY</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;PLEASE PHONE THE CHAUFFEURS ON 07894 405753, 10 - 15 minutes PRIOR TO YOUR ARRIVAL.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 North: Exit the M5 at Junction 18.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A4 towards Bristol and the airport for about 5 miles.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right onto the A38 and follow it to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs to the Drop Off Car Park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a ticket upon entry and follow the route to the left of the car park nearest the terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;You will be met by your chauffeur who will give you a contact number to use on your return.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 South: Exit the M5 at Junction 22.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A38 towards Weston Super Mare.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A38 for approximately 17 miles to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs to the Drop Off Car Park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a ticket upon entry and follow the route to the left of the car park nearest the terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;You will be met by your chauffeur who will give you a contact number to use on your return.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>Please phone the chauffeur on 07894 405753, 10 - 15 minutes prior to arrival at the airport. Upon arrival at the Drop Off Car Park adjacent to the terminal building. Take a ticket at the barrier. The chauffeur will meet you in this car park. Your car will be checked and return instructions given.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>When you return from your trip please phone the number given to you by the chauffeur, when you have cleared customs. Then make your way to the Drop Off Car Park adjacent to Arrivals, where your car will be ready for you to collect.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0871 334 4450</helpline><distanceToAirport>Your car will be parked in Bristol Airport's secure on-site car park for the duration of your trip.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>All of Bristol Airport's on-site car parks are well lit with security fencing, CCTV, automatic number plate registration and 24 hour staffing. They also hold the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has special assistance bays for Blue Badge holders and help buttons to call for assistance at the barriers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BRSI.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>BRSF</code><airport>BRS</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>BRISTOL SILVERZONE</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure on-site parking at Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Bristol Airport's Cheapest On-Site car park.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>Secure - on site parking.  &lt;br /&gt;Cheapest on-site parking.  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bristol Airport, Bristol, BS48 3DY</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 North: Exit the M5 at Junction 18.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A4 towards Bristol and the airport for about 5 miles.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right onto the A38 and follow it to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to the car park is located on the A38 on the right hand side shortly after the main entrance to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 South: Exit the M5 at Junction 22.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A38 towards Weston Super Mare.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A38 for approximately 17 miles to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to the car park is located on the A38 on the left hand side shortly before the main entrance to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>Once you have parked go to reception with your booking reference; flight numbers and the drop-off bay number. You will need to leave your keys with reception and then board the courtesy transfer bus.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Take the courtesy transfer bus back to the car park. Collect your keys from reception and return to your car. At the exit the barrier will rise automatically.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0871 334 4450</helpline><distanceToAirport>About 1&amp;frac12; miles from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Silverzone operate transfers to and from the airport terminal every 20 minutes which take just 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>All of Bristol Airport's on-site car parks are well lit with security fencing, CCTV, automatic number plate registration and 24 hour staffing. They also hold the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has special assistance bays for Blue Badge holders and help buttons to call for assistance at the barriers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BRSF.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>BRSG</code><airport>BRS</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>BRISTOL SILVERZONE SAVER</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure on-site parking at Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Extra savings for non-flexible booking.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>Secure on site parking  &lt;br /&gt;Extra savings - Non-flexible booking  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bristol Airport, Bristol, BS48 3DY</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE THAT THESE SAVER BOOKINGS ARE STRICTLY NON-AMENDABLE AND NON-REFUNDABLE.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 North: Exit the M5 at Junction 18.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A4 towards Bristol and the airport for about 5 miles.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right onto the A38 and follow it to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to the car park is located on the A38 on the right hand side shortly after the main entrance to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the M5 South: Exit the M5 at Junction 22.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A38 towards Weston Super Mare.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A38 for approximately 17 miles to Bristol Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to the car park is located on the A38 on the left hand side shortly before the main entrance to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>Once you have parked go to reception with your booking reference, flight numbers and the drop-off bay number. You will need to leave your keys with reception and then board the courtesy transfer bus.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Take the courtesy transfer bus back to the car park. Collect your keys from reception and return to your car. At the exit the barrier will rise automatically.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0871 334 4450</helpline><distanceToAirport>About 1.5 miles from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Silverzone operate transfers to and from the airport terminal every 20 minutes which take just 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>All of Bristol Airport's on-site car parks are well lit with security fencing, CCTV, automatic number plate registration and 24 hour staffing. They also hold the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has special assistance bays for Blue Badge holders and help buttons to call for assistance at the barriers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/BRSG.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"CWL\"><name>Cardiff Airport</name><shortname>cardiffairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>CWLB</code><airport>CWL</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>HIGHWAYMAN SECURE PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;The ONLY offsite parking for Cardiff Airport&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Transfers are every 15 minutes. A 5-7 minute transfer time&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The ONLY offsite parking Cardiff Airport&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;AA / Police Gold Award winning. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;24 hours a day&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Runs every 15 mins&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;5-7 min transfer&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; Highwayman Secure Parking,&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Nurston, Rhoose, Barry, Vale of Glamorgan,&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Cardiff, CF62 3BH&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; From M4: Exit M4 J33 signed Cardiff West Barry, Cardiff Airport &amp;nbsp;&amp;amp; A4232.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Join the A4232 and continue &amp;nbsp;for 3.3 miles. Leave the A4232 at the Culverhouse&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Cross interchange. At the r/about at the top of the slip road, take the 3rd exit signposted A4050,&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Wenvoe, Cardiff Airport &amp;amp; Barry. Continue on the A4050 for 3 miles, travelling straight across&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; 5 r/abouts. At the 6th r/about, take 2nd exit signed Cardiff &amp;nbsp;airport, heading towards St.Athan &amp;amp; LIantwit Major.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Continue straight &amp;nbsp;over 4 r/abouts joining B4265. Turn 1st left signposted Highwayman Inn.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Do not turn left up lane keep right into the village of Fonmon, past the duckpond.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Turn left into Port Road. Follow the road for 3/4 mile and the car park is located on the left hand side just past the Highwayman Inn.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; If you are using a Sat Nav please entre Nurston along with the post code CF62 3BH.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Arrive at the Highwayman Secure Parking where you will be greeted and checked in by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; a member of staff.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure></departureProcedure><openingPeriods></openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 01446 719105&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; The car park is a 5-7 minute bus ride to the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport></transferFromAirport><transferTime>Transfers take around 5-7 mins</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures></securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/CWLB.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"DSA\"><name>Doncaster Robin Hood Airport</name><shortname>doncasterrobinhoodairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>DSAG</code><airport>DSA</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>BLUE SKY PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;BRAND NEW!&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Only 3 minutes away from the Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Luxury courtesy shuttle transfer&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Less than 1.5 miles from the main Airport entrance.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;BRAND NEW!&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Only 3 mins away&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Luxury courtesy shuttle transfer&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Less than 1.5 miles from the main Airport entrance&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; Quarry Lane, Branton, Doncaster DN3 3RA&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;h3&gt; From the North and West Via M62&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Take the M62 eastbound towards HULL. Turn off the M62 at J35 and follow the M18 southbound towards Doncaster. Leave the M18 at J5 and head Eastbound on the M180, keep in the left hand lane as you will LEAVE the M180 almost immediately at junction 1.&lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt; From the East via the M180 / M18&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; When travelling from the EAST follow the M180 to the end (It's junction with the M18). At the roundabout follow it all the way around, coming back on yourself you are now heading East on the M180, keep in the LEFT LANE as you will leave the motorway immediately at junction 1, in only a few hundred yards !&lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt; From the South via the M1&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Take the M1 Northbound to junction 32, join the M18 and continue until junction 5. Take the M180 Eastbound, keep in the LEFT LANE as you will leave the motorway immediately at J1 in only a few hundred yards!&lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt; Local Directions after leaving the M180&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; At the roundabout after you have left the M180, turn right and join the A18 to wards Doncaster. After half a mile turn left A614 to BAWTRY opposite the GREEN TREE pub. Travel through Hatfield Woodhouse continue a further 3 miles to BLAXTON.&lt;br /&gt; At the roundabout with the BLUE BELL pub on your left, TURN RIGHT towards AUCKLEY / BRANTON. (At this point you will have seen signs for ROBIN HOOD AIRPORT).&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Go past WALKERS NURSERY on your left, through the traffic lights, and continue into and through AUCKLEY and after 1/4 of a mile you will enter BRANTON. Go past the THREE HORSE SHOES PUB on your left. 200 yards past the pub on your left is ATTENBOROUGH CARS. Immediately turn into QUARRY LANE and we are situated to the rear of the car sales.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The car park gate will be on your left, and reception is at the rear of the building. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; When you arrive, park your car and head to reception with your confirmation booking. Give your keys to them and they will store it in a secured location. Then, catch the free bus to the airport. The transfer runs when needed and takes 3 minutes.&lt;br /&gt; Make sure you allow enough time for your journey as the car park can be busy during peak periods.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Once you have cleared customs ring the car park to announce your arrival and proceed to the meeting point.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 07584 666616.&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; Blue Sky Parking is 1.5 miles from the airport.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; The car parks luxury courtesy shuttle will take you to the airport in just 3 minutes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>3 Minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; Our site is well fenced, has 24 hour CCTV coverage and in this regard we will endeavour to take care of your vehicle whilst it is in our care, however we do have public access to our site and as such we cannot accepts liability for any damage or loss. You must have a valid certificate of insurance which covers your vehicle whilst it is in our care.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>&lt;p&gt; There are no limits on vehicle size or height.&lt;/p&gt;</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Unfortunately, there are no disabled facilities.&lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/DSAG.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>DSAC</code><airport>DSA</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Located directly in front of the terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Secure parking just a couple of minutes' walk from the check in hall.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Opposite Terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Operates Automatic Number Plate Recognition system (ANPR)&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;2-3 minutes walk.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keep your keys.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Doncaster Robin Hood Airport, DN9 3RH.</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the A1: Leave the A1(M) at Junction 34 (Blyth).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the roundabout take the A614 heading towards Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The A614 runs into the A638 through Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A638 through Bawtry, heading north towards Doncaster.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Approximately 3&amp;frac12; miles after leaving Bawtry take a right turn into Hurst Lane, signposted for Auckley.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Proceed along Hurst Lane for approximately 1&amp;frac12; miles until you arrive at a set of traffic lights.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right at these lights and continue forward along the dual carriageway towards Robin Hood Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the West via the M62: Turn off the M62 at Junction 35 and follow the M18 southbound.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Leave the M18 at Junction 5 and head eastbound on the M180, leaving almost immediately at Junction 1.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a right turn at the roundabout, heading south towards the A614 signposted for Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the A614 and Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Travel through Hatfield Woodhouse and continue for approximately two miles into Blaxton.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the Blaxton roundabout turn right and follow the road, passing Walkers Nursery/Garden Centre on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the next left into Gatehouse Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;After crossing the railway line take the right turn at the roundabout and continue for approximately 200 yards.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to Robin Hood Airport is on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport, keeping the terminal building on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the East via the M180/M18: Follow the M180 to the end.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the roundabout, take the right hand lane and follow it all the way around, coming back on yourself so you are now heading eastbound on the M180 towards Scunthorpe.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Leave the motorway at Junction 1.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a right turn at the roundabout, heading south towards the A614 signposted for Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the A614 and Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Travel through Hatfield Woodhouse and continue for approximately two miles into Blaxton.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the Blaxton roundabout turn right and follow the road, passing Walkers Nursery/Garden Centre on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the next left into Gatehouse Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;After crossing the railway line take the right turn at the roundabout and continue for approximately 200 yards.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to Robin Hood Airport is on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport, keeping the terminal building on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>This car park operates an Automatic Number Plate Recognition system (ANPR). Please DO NOT insert a credit/debit card into the car park barrier as you will be charged again. Upon arrival at the car park, drive up to the entry barrier. The ANPR system will read the vehicle registration plate and automatically issue you with a ticket. (Please wait about 20 seconds for this process.) Remove the ticket, and the barrier will rise allowing you to enter. Please retain the ticket and keep it safe as you will need this to exit. Should the system fail to recognise your vehicle or the barrier does not rise for you automatically, please press for a ticket.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return to the airport, please collect your vehicle and drive to the exit barriers. Insert the original entry ticket in the exit machine, and wait whilst the ANPR system reads your vehicle registration and ticket. The barrier will then rise allowing you to exit the car park. If the system failed to recognise your vehicle when you arrived at the airport, please press the help button on the barrier and provide the operator with your pre-booking reference number and surname. The operator will then raise the barrier manually for you to exit.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; This car park is opened 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>0844 871 7496</helpline><distanceToAirport>The Car Park is located within the airport boundary, a short walking distance away from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required as the car park is just a short walk from the terminal.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; This is an official on-airport car park, managed by Robin Hood Airport. They have high levels of security, with a high-tech CCTV system, electronically controlled entry and exit barriers, Automatic Number Plate Recognition, and 24 hour monitoring. All of the on-airport car parks at Robin Hood Airport hold the 'Park Mark' award for safer parking.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>&lt;p&gt; There are no height restrictions at this car park, however please note that they do not allow trailers, or coaches. Any vehicles requiring more than one space must be booked via their call centre on 0845 319 2781.&lt;/p&gt;</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Disabled parking spaces are located in all of our On-Airport Car Parks . Individual spaces cannot be reserved and are&amp;nbsp;always subject to availability.&lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/DSAC.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>DSAD</code><airport>DSA</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY PRICEBUSTER</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Located directly in front of the terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Extra savings for non-flexible bookings.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Doncaster Robin Hood Airport, DN9 3RH.</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the A1: Leave the A1(M) at Junction 34 (Blyth).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the roundabout take the A614 heading towards Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The A614 runs into the A638 through Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A638 through Bawtry, heading north towards Doncaster.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Approximately 3&amp;frac12; miles after leaving Bawtry take a right turn into Hurst Lane, signposted for Auckley.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Proceed along Hurst Lane for approximately 1&amp;frac12; miles until you arrive at a set of traffic lights.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn right at these lights and continue forward along the dual carriageway towards Robin Hood Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the West via the M62: Turn off the M62 at Junction 35 and follow the M18 southbound.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Leave the M18 at Junction 5 and head eastbound on the M180, leaving almost immediately at Junction 1.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a right turn at the roundabout, heading south towards the A614 signposted for Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the A614 and Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Travel through Hatfield Woodhouse and continue for approximately two miles into Blaxton.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the Blaxton roundabout turn right and follow the road, passing Walkers Nursery/Garden Centre on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the next left into Gatehouse Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;After crossing the railway line take the right turn at the roundabout and continue for approximately 200 yards.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to Robin Hood Airport is on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport, keeping the terminal building on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the East via the M180/M18: Follow the M180 to the end.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the roundabout, take the right hand lane and follow it all the way around, coming back on yourself so you are now heading eastbound on the M180 towards Scunthorpe.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Leave the motorway at Junction 1.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take a right turn at the roundabout, heading south towards the A614 signposted for Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the A614 and Bawtry.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Travel through Hatfield Woodhouse and continue for approximately two miles into Blaxton.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the Blaxton roundabout turn right and follow the road, passing Walkers Nursery/Garden Centre on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the next left into Gatehouse Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;After crossing the railway line take the right turn at the roundabout and continue for approximately 200 yards.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The entrance to Robin Hood Airport is on the left.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs for the 'Car Park' on approach to the Airport, keeping the terminal building on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>This car park operates an Automatic Number Plate Recognition system (ANPR). Please DO NOT insert a credit/debit card into the car park barrier as you will be charged again. Upon arrival at the car park, drive up to the entry barrier. The ANPR system will read the vehicle registration plate and automatically issue you with a ticket. (Please wait about 20 seconds for this process.) Remove the ticket, and the barrier will rise allowing you to enter. Please retain the ticket and keep it safe as you will need this to exit. Should the system fail to recognise your vehicle or the barrier does not rise for you automatically, please press for a ticket.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return to the airport, please collect your vehicle and drive to the exit barriers. Insert the original entry ticket in the exit machine, and wait whilst the ANPR system reads your vehicle registration and ticket. The barrier will then rise allowing you to exit the car park. If the system failed to recognise your vehicle when you arrived at the airport, please press the help button on the barrier and provide the operator with your pre-booking reference number and surname. The operator will then raise the barrier manually for you to exit.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; This car park is opened 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>0844 871 7496</helpline><distanceToAirport>The Price Buster Long Stay Car Park is located within the airport b