ly easy thing about coming back from holiday. Then just go to reception with your booking confirmation and pick up your keys. A member of staff will open the barrier and the gates to let you out.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 24hrs a day, 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 0113 250 6669&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; The Airport is 2 minutes away from the car park.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Airport transfers run on demand, 24 hours a day, and take just two minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>2 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park has an eight-foot-tall fence, gates, CCTV cameras, barriers, floodlighting, staff on-site 24 hours a day and the Park Mark security award from the police.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>&lt;p&gt; Caravans and motorhomes can't be parked undercover. Beyond that, there is no maximum car size.&lt;/p&gt;</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; This package is great for disabled customers as there are no transfers.&lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LBAB.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LBAA</code><airport>LBA</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>SENTINEL SECURITY CAR PARK</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Award winning customer service.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Only 2 minutes from the Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Established for 19 years.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Park Mark security awarded car park.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Only 2 mins from the Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Established for 19 years.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Park Mark Security awarded Car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Warren House Lane, Yeadon,,West Yorkshire, LS19 7FT</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the A658 (North): Follow the signs for the airport and when you reach the roundabout with the airport on the left, turn right onto Warren House Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Sentinel Security is located 200 yards along on the right hand side.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the A658 (South): Follow the signs for the airport and when you reach the roundabout at the end of a tunnel, with the airport on the right, turn left onto Warren House Lane.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Sentinel Security is located 200 yards along on the right hand side.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival, drive to reception and park in one of the designated spaces facing the large Sentinel sign. Check in at reception and board the minibus that will transfer you to the terminal.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Return details will be provided on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 24hrs a day, 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0113 239 1555 Vat No. 726 0035 69</helpline><distanceToAirport>Sentinel Security is located &amp;frac12; a mile from the Airport Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Sentinel Security operate transfers to and from the airport on demand which take just 2 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>2 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Sentinel Security has round the clock security guards, CCTV and is floodlit at night. The car park also holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LBAA.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"LPL\"><name>Liverpool International Airport</name><shortname>liverpoolinternationalairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>LPLI</code><airport>LPL</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>APL LIVERPOOL OUTDOOR</name><description>&lt;li&gt;90 second transfer service available on demand.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Excellent Service&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;90 second Transfer&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Available on demand&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Transfer to terminal are charged at &amp;pound;2.00 per person. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>APL Outdoor Parking, 21 Skypark International, Speke Hall Avenue, Liverpool, L24 1YL</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the North/North East:&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take M6 southbound to Junction 21A and follow signs for M62 West.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At Junction 6 turn onto the A5300 towards A561 and follow signs for Liverpool John Lennon Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;When you reach Speke Hall Avenue - the approach road to the Airport - Skypark International Business Park is on the right approx 500 metres before you get to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Simply make a U-turn at the airport and drive back up the same road, turn left into Skypark International.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;APL Parking Ltd's reception is immediately ahead at Unit 21/22.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the South/South East:&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow M6 northbound to Junction 20 and turn onto M56 in the direction of Widnes/Chester.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At Junction 12 of M56 turn onto A557/A562 and take the dual carriageway via Runcorn Bridge, which merges with A561, and follow signs for Liverpool John Lennon Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;When you reach Speke Hall Avenue - the approach road to the Airport - Skypark International Business Park is on the right approx 500 metres before you get to the airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Simply make a U-turn at the airport and drive back up the same road, turn left into Skypark International.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;APL Parking Ltd's reception is immediately ahead at Unit 21/22. &lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From North Wales:&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A55 and then join the M56 Eastbound to Junction 12. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then follow the directions From the South/South East as above.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival at the car park please report to reception and present your booking confirmation or reference number.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full return instructions will be given on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>APL Liverpool Outdoor is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>07776 232507</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located less than 500 metres from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; APL Liverpool Outdoor operate transfers to and from the airport on demand which take just 90 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;pound;2.00 Exit Fees per Booking are payable on Arrival at our Reception to cover the Exit Fees for your respective “Arrival” and “Return” Shuttle journeys to and from the Airport.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>90 Seconds</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>APL Liverpool Parking has 24 hour security patrols; security/crash barriers; CCTV surveillance and full perimeter security fencing.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>Skypark Liverpool cannot accept the following vehicles: lorries; mobile homes; or commercial vehicles.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>APL Liverpool Parking has spacious and accessible disabled toilet facilities. The car park's staff will provide assistance where required.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LPLI.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LPLH</code><airport>LPL</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>IMAGINE LIVERPOOL OUTDOOR</name><description>&lt;li&gt;90 second transfer service available on demand.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Excellent Service&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;90 second Transfer&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Available on demand&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Imagine Liverpool Outdoor Parking, 3-4 Morrow Court, Skypark Industrial Estate, Speke, Liverpool, L24 1YD</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At Speke Hall Avenue: Take the airport approach road (Speke Hall Avenue).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the end of the dual carriageway, do not turn left into the airport but go around the roundabout and return back along the dual carriageway.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the first left at the post box.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Imagine are the first building on the right opposite Enterprise.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the North/North East: Take the M6 to J21a and take the M62 west to J6.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A5300 and then the A561.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then follow the signs to the airport and follow the directions as above.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the South/South East: Take the M6 to J20 and take the M56 west to J12.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the A557/A562 via the Runcorn Bridge to merge with the A561.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then follow the signs to the airport and follow the directions as above.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the Wirral: At peak times it may be quicker to use the M53/M56 and follow the directions above.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From North Wales: Take the A55 and then join the M56 Eastbound to J12.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then follow the directions as above.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;SAT NAV POSTCODE: L24 1YL (Owen Drive)&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;IF YOU HAVE ANY TROUBLE FINDING THE CAR PARK, PLEASE CALL IMAGINE ON 0151 486 7247 or 07977 062209, ANYTIME 24 HOURS A DAY.&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival at the car park please report to reception and present your booking confirmation or reference number.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full return instructions will be given on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Imagine Liverpool Meet &amp;amp; Greet is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0151 486 7247</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located 400 metres from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Imagine Liverpool Outdoor&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; The car park's transfer bus will take you to the airport and drop you at the airport's bus stop near the terminal, whenever needed, 24 hours a day. It takes just 90 seconds and costs &amp;pound;2. You can walk it in 9 minutes, but we'd recommend taking the bus as it's much easier.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>90 Seconds</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Imagine Parking is manned 24 hours a day and is monitored by 24 hour CCTV surveillance. The car park is patrolled by guard dogs and has been awarded the 'Park Mark' Safer Parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>4</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LPLH.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LPLP</code><airport>LPL</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>IPARK LIVERPOOL</name><description>&lt;li&gt; Safe, Secure &amp;amp; Convenient.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Within walking distance of the terminal building.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Extra savings for non-flexible bookings.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Safe, Secure &amp;amp; Convenient.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Within walking distance.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Extra saving - Non flexible booking.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Operates Automatic Number Plate Recognition System (ANPR)&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Awarded the Park Mark security award by the British Parking Association.&lt;br /&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; IPARK Liverpool. Liverpool John Lennon Airport, L24 1YD&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; Travelling from the North / North-East&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; M6 southbound to junction 21A with M62. Please note that junction 21A is a split junction, and motorists should ensure they come off at the slip road signposted Liverpool. Follow M62 West to junction 6 onto the A5300 to the A561 and follow signs to the Airport, which is situated off Speke Hall Avenue.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Travelling from the South / East&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; M6 northbound to junction 20 with M56. Follow M56 to junction 12 onto A557/A562 dual carriageway via Runcorn Bridge to merge with A561. Follow signs to the Airport, situated off Speke Hall Avenue.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Travelling from the Wirral / North Wales&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Passengers travelling from Wirral may find it more convenient at peak times to use the M53 and then the M56 (as instructions from the South / East) rather than a route through the City Centre of Liverpool via the Mersey Tunnels. Passengers travelling from North Wales should join the A55 to connect with the M56 eastbound, and then follow instructions as from the East.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Drive up to the entry barrier, the ANPR system will read your vehicle registration number and automatically issue you with a ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Drive to the exit barrier and insert your car park ticket. The barrier will rise automatically allowing you to exit.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 0845 319 0421&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; Ipark Liverpool - &amp;nbsp;Car Park is located &amp;nbsp;6-7 minutes walking distance from the terminal building.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Transfers are not required as the car park is 6-7 minutes walk from the Terminal Building.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;ol&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Awarded the Park Mark security award by the British Parking Association&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Boasts 24/7 CCTV coverage, secure fencing and is patrolled 24 hours a day.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Operates Automatic Number Plate Recognition System (ANPR) making your visit as easy and convenient as possible.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Self-Park - you don’t need to leave your keys with a stranger; you park your own car and keep your keys with you!&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ol&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>&lt;p&gt; We have no height restrictions in this car park. However, please not we do not allow trailers, or coaches unless they have pre-notified the airport. Any vehicles requiring more than one space must make a booking via the call centre; 0845 319 0421.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHou