tanceToAirport>Gatwick APH is located about 7 miles from the airport terminals.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>APH operate transfers to and from the airport every 15 minutes which take 15 minutes</transferFromAirport><transferTime>10 - 15 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Gatwick APH has barrier control, CCTV and has the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>There is a height restriction at the car park of 2.4 meters (or 7ft 6&amp;quot;). Vans are only accepted if they fit into a normal parking space. Trailers are not accepted at this car park.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>Facilities for disabled are available. Please email or phone direct for more details.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWW.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWJ</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>COPHALL PARKING GATWICK LTD</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Friendly, award-winning, off-airport parking with over 30 years experience.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;10 minute transfer to airport on our Courtesy Buses. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Free transfer run on request 24 hours.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;This compound is fully insured, alarmed and manned 24 hours a day.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Effingham Road, Copthorne, West Sussex, RH10 3HZ</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;Please arrive at least 30 minutes before your flight check-in time.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Travelling from the South/West via the M23: &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 10, sign posted Crawley.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Take the A264 for East Grinstead.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Go straight over the next roundabout and continue for 1&amp;frac12; miles.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;At the next roundabout take the 1st exit the B2028 for Lingfield.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;At the next roundabout turn left onto the B2037.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;After &amp;frac14; of a mile you will pass the Curious Pig Pub on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Cophall Parking Gatwick is the next turning on your right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Travelling from the East via the M25: &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Exit the M25 at Junction 6, sign posted Godstone.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Follow the A22 towards East Grinstead.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;After 7&amp;frac12; miles you will reach a roundabout with a Mormon Temple ahead of you.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Take the 3rd exit onto the B2028.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Follow this road until you reach the roundabout and turn right onto the B2037.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;After &amp;frac14; of a mile you will pass the Curious Pig Pub on your left.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Cophall Parking Gatwick is the next turning on your right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival please report to reception with your booking confirmation or booking reference number. Please arrive at least 30 minutes before your flight check-in time.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full return instructions will be provided on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Cophall Parking Gatwick is open 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Closed Christmas day.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt;01342 712779&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;FAX: 01342 719996&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>Cophall Parking Gatwick Ltd is located about 7 miles from the airport terminals.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Cophall Parking Gatwick offers on demand courtesy transfers to and from the airport which take 10-15 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>10 - 15 Minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Cophall Parking Gatwick has CCTV, is manned 24 hours a day and has the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has disabled toilet facilities. Reception is wheel-chair accessible and the transfer buses are suitable for disabled passengers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWJ.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWQ</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>I LOVE MEET AND GREET</name><description>&lt;li&gt;30 years experience of running Meet and Greet at Gatwick.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Approved Gatwick operator.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Buy With Confidence Accreditation.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt; Prompt Service&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Airport Approved Meet and Greet Operator.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Collection &amp;amp; return at both terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Prompt Service.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; I Love Meet &amp;amp; Greet Ltd, Povey Cross Road, RH6 0BE&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes away from arriving at the airport.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Gatwick Airport has implemented a new forecourt access policy which comes in to effect from 1st July 2013. Please ensure you inform any Traffic Wardens that you are using I Love Meet and Greet service, who have a licence to operate on the forecourts. Please print your confirmation and make sure it is placed on your dashboard in full view.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the M23: Exit at Junction 9.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs to either the North or South Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow signs to 'Passenger Drop Off' at the appropriate Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Keep in the right hand lane and head to the far end where a driver will meet you.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; North Terminal: Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes from the airport. Follow signs to 'passenger drop off' at the North Terminal, keeping in the right hand land and head to the far end where a driver will meet you. Emergency number: 07805927969.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Please ensure your printed confirmation is placed on your dashboard in full view of any Traffic Wardens.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; South Terminal: Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes from the airport. Follow signs to 'passenger drop off' at the South Terminal, keeping in the right hand land and head to the far end where a driver will meet you. Emergency number: 07805927969. Please ensure your printed confirmation is placed on your dashboard in full view of any Traffic Wardens.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; North Terminal: To ensure all our clients have a fast and efficient service, please collect all your luggage, clear customs and when you are in the arrivals hall call 01293 824221 (select option 1) to have your car delivered. There is a no waiting policy at this terminal so please ensure you are ready to collect your car when you call. Exit the building on the ground floor, walk between the 2 cars parks opposite and wait in the far end of the set down area. Emergency number: 07805 927969.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; South Terminal: To ensure all our clients have a fast and efficient service, please collect all your luggage, clear customs and when you are in the arrivals hall call 01293 824221 (select option 1) to have your car delivered. There is a no waiting policy at this terminal so please ensure you are ready to collect your car when you call. Follow signs for 'Courtesy Coaches', exit the building and take a lift down to the ground floor. Cross to the outside lane where your car will be delivered to you. Emergency number: 07805 927969.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Purple Parking Meet &amp;amp; Greet is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 01293 824221&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; EMERGENCY NUMBER: 07805927969&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; FAX: 01293 515767&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located adjacent to the airport and less than 3 miles from the terminals.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park is manned 24 hours a day and has peripheral fencing, lighting, locked gates and CCTV. The car park holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWQ.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWL</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY NORTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Service only available for North Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Fully secure.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Awarded the Park Mark Safer Parking Award. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;24 hour staff.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;CCTV on site. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0RN</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Go straight ahead at the first roundabout (J9a) following signs for the North Terminal..&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the next roundabout take the third exit signposted Long Stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Proceed past the BP petrol station on the right and go straight over the next small roundabout.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the road for 1.1km (0.69 miles) to the next roundabout, and turn right into the Long Stay North Terminal car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On entry to the Long Stay North car park, pull up to the barrier where your number plate will be scanned. If you are recognised a ticket with booking reference above bar code will be printed. If not, press for a ticket. Follow sign to zone indicated, park and board bus.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for &amp;quot;Long Term car parks&amp;quot;. Coaches are located at the bus stop on the left as you exit the terminal on the lower forecourt. Please tell the coach driver where you have parked (ie Zone E Bus Stop 3). If you have a reference number above the bar code on your ticket proceed straight to the exit barrier. Otherwise, please call in to reception, adjacent to the exit, with your ticket and booking details.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>08448 118311</helpline><distanceToAirport>Long Stay North is located at the airport and is just 5 minutes from the North Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Courtesy coach transfers to and from the North Terminal operate 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Transfers operate every 10 minutes and take 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>4</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWL.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGW2</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY NORTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keep your keys.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;5 mins transfer.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Operates 24 hours.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Transfer only available for North Terminal.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0RN</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Go straight ahead at the first roundabout (J9a) following signs for the North Terminal..&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the next roundabout take the third exit signposted Long Stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Proceed past the BP petrol station on the right and go straight over the next small roundabout.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the road for 1.1km (0.69 miles) to the next roundabout, and turn right into the Long Stay North Terminal car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On entry to the Long Stay North car park, pull up to the barrier where your number plate will be scanned. If you are recognised a ticket with booking reference above bar code will be printed. If not, press for a ticket. Follow sign to zone indicated, park and board bus.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for &amp;quot;Long Term car parks&amp;quot;. Coaches are located at the bus stop on the left as you exit the terminal on the lower forecourt. Please tell the coach driver where you have parked (ie Zone E Bus Stop 3). If you have a reference number above the bar code on your ticket proceed straight to the exit barrier. Otherwise, please call in to reception, adjacent to the exit, with your ticket and booking details.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>08448 118311</helpline><distanceToAirport>Long Stay North is located at the airport and is just 5 minutes from the North Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Courtesy coach transfers to and from the North Terminal operate 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Transfers operate every 10 minutes and take 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>4</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGW2.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWM</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY PLUS GATWICK</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;For faster parking, we park your car for you.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation></furtherInformation><address>South Terminal, Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0NN</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keeping on the inside lane exit left at the next roundabout following signs for the South Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then take the second exit on the left, sign-posted Long Stay Plus (previously Parking Plus).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the end of this road, turn left following signs for Long Stay Plus.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>For faster parking, we park your car for you. On arrival the barrier will open automatically. Proceed to Reception. You will be asked to leave your voucher/car keys and you will receive a receipt. Your vehicle will be parked by the valet staff leaving you to board the courtesy coach.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for Long Stay Car Parks to the Bus Stops on the Upper forecourt. On your return to the car park, go to Reception with the receipt issued on entry and exchange this for your keys. Your car will be parked in a bay close by.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>08448 118311</helpline><distanceToAirport>Long Stay Plus is located at the airport and is just 2 minutes from the South Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Courtesy coach transfers to and from the South Terminal operate 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Transfers operate every 10 minutes and take 2 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>2 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWM.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWK</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY SOUTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Long Stay South is manned 24 hours.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Frequently patrolled. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Enclosed by security fencing.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;CCTV in place. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Has been awarded the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0NZ</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keeping on the inside lane exit left at the next roundabout following signs for the South Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then take the second exit on the left, sign-posted Long Stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow signs for the Long Stay South (previously Parking Express) car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Bear right until you reach the entrance barrier for the Long Stay South car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On entry to the Long Stay South car park, take a ticket and follow signs to the zone indicated. Make a note of zone and nearest bus stop. Your booking reference will be printed on the ticket. If instead it says &amp;quot;Cashier&amp;quot;, report to customer services on your return.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for Long Stay car parks to the Bus Stops. Before boarding the coach check it is going to the zone you have parked in and tell the driver which zone you require. To exit the car park, insert your entry ticket into the machine at the barrier. Your number plate will be read and the barrier will lift automatically. If your ticket has &amp;quot;Cashier&amp;quot; printed on it, report to customer services by the exit.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>08448 118311</helpline><distanceToAirport>Long Stay South is located at the airport and is just 5 minutes from the South Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Courtesy coach transfers to and from the South Terminal operate 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Transfers operate every 10 minutes and take 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>24</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWK.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGW1</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>LONG STAY SOUTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keep your keys.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;5 min transfer.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Only transfer to South Terminal&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0NZ</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Keeping on the inside lane exit left at the next roundabout following signs for the South Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Then take the second exit on the left, sign-posted Long Stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow signs for the Long Stay South (previously Parking Express) car park.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Bear right until you reach the entrance barrier for the Long Stay South car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On entry to the Long Stay South car park, take a ticket and follow signs to the zone indicated. Make a note of zone and nearest bus stop. Your booking reference will be printed on the ticket. If instead it says &amp;quot;Cashier&amp;quot;, report to customer services on your return.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for Long Stay car parks to the Bus Stops. Before boarding the coach check it is going to the zone you have parked in and tell the driver which zone you require. To exit the car park, insert your entry ticket into the machine at the barrier. Your number plate will be read and the barrier will lift automatically. If your ticket has &amp;quot;Cashier&amp;quot; printed on it, report to customer services by the exit.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>08448 118311</helpline><distanceToAirport>Long Stay South is located at the airport and is just 5 minutes from the South Terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Courtesy coach transfers to and from the South Terminal operate 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Transfers operate every 10 minutes and take 5 minutes.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>5 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>4</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGW1.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWG</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>METEOR MEET AND GREET PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Hassle-free chauffeur service - your vehicle is collected and returned to you at the airport.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Hassle-free chauffeur service.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;No transfer required.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;This car park holds the Park Mark award for secure parking.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Fully secured and has CCTV; 24 hour patrols.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Meteor Meet &amp;amp; Greet Parking, PO Box 298, RH6 7YD</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; IMPORTANT - PLEASE CALL 0333 577 0943 WHEN YOU ARE 15 MINUTES AWAY FROM THE AIRPORT TO CONFIRM YOUR MEET TIME WITH YOUR DRIVER. FAILURE TO CALL MAY RESULT IN A DELAY.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; From the M23: Drive to Junction 9 and follow the signs to either the North or South Terminal.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; FOR SOUTH TERMINAL:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs to Car Set-Down (Ground Level) and park at the far end just after the last pedestrian crossing.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Emergency Helpline: 07805 067348.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; FOR NORTH TERMINAL:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs to Departures Set Down &amp;amp; Passenger Drop Off.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Our driver will meet you at the far end.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Emergency Helpline: 07805 067348.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; NORTH TERMINAL&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; OUTBOUND &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Please call 0333 577 0943 fifteen minutes before arriving at the airport. Follow signs to Departures set down and passenger drop off and our driver will meet you at the far end.&amp;nbsp; A No Waiting policy is in force.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Post Code: North Terminal RH6 0PJ&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Should you arrive 30 mins or more outside of your specified arrival times, you may be subject to delays.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Emergency Helpline is 07805 067348.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; SOUTH TERMINAL&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; OUTBOUND &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Please call 0333 577 0943 fifteen minutes before arriving at the airport. Follow signs to Departures set down and passenger drop off and our driver will meet you at the far end.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Post Codes: South Terminal RH6 0NP&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Should you arrive 30 mins or more outside of your specified arrival times, you may be subject to delays.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Emergency Helpline is 07805 067348.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; A No Waiting policy is in force at both terminals.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; For South Terminal: Please collect your luggage, clear Customs and then call 0333 577 0943. Follow signs to Short Stay ORANGE Car Park, go down the lift to Level 1 and make your way to the Approved Operators Parking Bays where our driver will meet you with your vehicle. Emergency no. is 07805 067348.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; For North Terminal: - Please collect luggage, clear customs and then call 0333 577 0943.&lt;br /&gt; Exit the building on the ground floor and make your way to the Approved Operators Area, opposite the Premier Inn, where your vehicle was collected/dropped off.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; This is due to the ongoing closure of the short term car park at North Terminal.&lt;br /&gt; Emergency Helpline is 07805 067348.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Non- Flex Meet &amp;amp; Greet is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 0333 577 0699 - option 1&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>Our main secure parking area is situated just under two miles from the terminals.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; Non- Flex&amp;nbsp; will store your car in a fully secured car park that has CCTV and 24 hour patrols.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWG.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWS</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>METEOR NON-FLEX MEET AND GREET</name><description>&lt;li&gt;A competitively priced personal service from friendly uniformed drivers.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Extra savings for non-flexible bookings.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Extra savings - Non flexible booking. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Meet &amp;amp; Return at terminal&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;No transfer required&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>P.O. Box 298, RH6 7YD</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; Please call 0333 5770943 when you are 15 minutes away from the airport to confirm your meet time with your driver. Failure to call may result in a delay in collecting your vehicle.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From London or Brighton: Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs to your Departure Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; For South Terminal: Follow the signs to Car Set-Down (Ground Level) and park at the far end just after the last pedestrian crossing.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Emergency Helpline: 07805 067348.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; For North Terminal: Follow the signs to Set Down and Passenger Drop-Off and the driver will meet you at the far end.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Emergency Helpline: 07805 067348.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Please call 0333 5770943 when you are 15 minutes away from the airport to confirm your meet time with your driver. Failure to call may result in a delay in collecting your vehicle. On your arrival at your Departure Terminal, please make your way to the appropriate meeting point where your driver will be waiting for you. The driver will be wearing a black Meteor Meet &amp;amp; Greet Parking shirt and black trousers.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; A No Waiting policy is in force at both terminals. Please collect your luggage and clear customs before calling 0333 5770943. Emergency No: 07805 067348.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; NORTH Terminal - Please collect luggage, clear customs and then call 0333 577 0943.&lt;br /&gt; Exit the building on the ground floor and make your way to the Approved Operators Area, opposite the Premier Inn, where your vehicle was collected/dropped off.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; This is due to the ongoing closure of the short term car park at North Terminal.&lt;br /&gt; Emergency Helpline is 07805 067348.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; SOUTH Terminal -Please collect luggage, clear customs and then call 0333 577 0943. Follow signs to Short Stay ORANGE Car Park, go down the lift to Level 1 and make your way to the Approved Operators Parking Bays where our driver will meet you with your vehicle.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Non- Flex Meet &amp;amp; Greet is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 0333 577 0699 - option 1&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; Non -Flex&amp;nbsp; main secure parking area is situated less than 2 miles from the airport.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required as this is a meet and greet service.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; Non- Flex&amp;nbsp; will store your car in a fully secured car park that has CCTV and 24 hour patrols.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWS.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGW6</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>PURPLE PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;CUSTOMER FAVOURITE!&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Less than 3 miles from the Airport.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Purple Parking is right next to the runway&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;As convenient as any on-airport car park but at an off-airport price.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;CUSTOMER FAVOURITE!&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Less than 3 miles from Airport&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Service operates to both Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Charlwood Rd, Lowfield Heath, Crawley, West Sussex, RH11 0QB</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; From the M23 - Junction 9:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Exit the motorway and follow the signs for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the motorway roundabout with traffic lights take the 2nd exit and head towards the airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout go straight over towards the North Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout take the 4th exit heading towards Crawley/Redhill (A23).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Join the dual carriageway and carry on until the next roundabout (Longbridge Roundabout) and take the 4th exit heading back on the A23 towards Gatwick, Brighton &amp;amp; Crawley.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Carry on over the next roundabout staying on the A23 Southbound.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the 2nd roundabout take the 2nd exit onto the Old Brighton Road South (Lowfield Heath/Charlwood).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Turn left at the mini-roundabout onto Charlwood Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Purple Parking is located 1&amp;frac12; miles ahead on the right hand side.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; From the M23 - Junction 10:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Exit the motorway and take the 3rd exit signposted Crawley (A2011).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the 1st roundabout take the 3rd exit signposted A2011 for Horsham.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout with traffic lights take the 4th exit towards Redhill/Gatwick (A23 Northbound)&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Carry on over the next roundabout following the signs for Gatwick.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout take the 1st exit for Lowfield Heath/Charlwood.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Turn left at the mini-roundabout onto Charlwood Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Purple Parking is located 1&amp;frac12; miles ahead on the right hand side.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; PLEASE NOTE: You will be required to leave your keys with reception as they will park your car whilst you transfer to the airport. Please also note that some Sat Nav devices aren't accurate enough with just the postcode, so please enter the full address.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; On arrival at Purple Parking, keep to the left hand lane and drive through the automatic barrier. Park in one of the arrival bays and note the lane number. Go to Reception and present them with your booking confirmation or booking reference and car and flight details. Place your keys in the red key box with the corresponding lane number and then take the bus to your terminal. The bus leaves from the Reception area and calls at both terminals. We recommend that you allow 45 minutes from checking into the car park to reaching the airport terminal.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt;Catch the transfer bus from where you were dropped off. You'll need to show the ticket you were given at check-in to the driver.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;If you're at the South Terminal, turn left out of the terminal and wait at bus stop 7 or 8, about 25 yards from the exit.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;If you're at the North Terminal, turn right out of the terminal and follow signs for buses. Wait at bus stop 6 or 7.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;After you've collected your keys from reception, drive to the exit and scan the barcode attached to your keys at the exit barrier to get out.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Airparks Gatwick is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>01293 842 901 Vat No. 726 0035 69</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; Purple Parking is located 3 miles from the airport terminals.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Purple Parking operate transfers to and from the airport every 15 minutes which take 10 - 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>10 - 15 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Airparks Gatwick has CCTV and 24-hour staffing. This car park has been awarded the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>Mini buses, high sided vehicles, mobile homes, lorries, caravans and trailers are not permitted.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>All buses are fully DDA compliant and are suitable for wheelchair use. Assistance with your luggage is available if required from the bus driver.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGW6.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWR</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>PURPLE PARKING MEET AND GREET</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Provided by a Gatwick Approved Operator&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;With 30 years' experience of meet and greet&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Holders of 'Buy With Confidence' Accreditation.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt; Prompt, professional valet parking service&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Provided by Gatwick Approved Operator&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Prompt &amp;amp; Professional valet parking service. &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Holders of 'Buy with Confidence' Accreditation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; Povey Cross Road, RH6 0BE&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes away from arriving at the airport.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; Gatwick Airport has implemented a new forecourt access policy which comes in to effect from the 1st July 2013. Please ensure you inform any Traffic Wardens that you are using I Love meet and greet service, who have a licence to operate on the forecourts. Please print your confirmation and make sure it is placed on your dashboard in full view.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the M23: Exit at Junction 9.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the signs to either the North or South Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow signs to 'Passenger Drop Off'' at the appropriate terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Keep in the right hand lane and head to the far end where a driver will meet you.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; North Terminal: Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes from the airport. Follow signs to 'passenger drop off' at the North Terminal, keeping in the right hand land and head to the far end where a driver will meet you. Emergency number: 07805927969. Please ensure your printed confirmation is placed on your dashboard in full view of any Traffic Wardens.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; South Terminal: Please call 01293 824221 (select option 1) when you are 10 minutes from the airport. Follow signs to 'passenger drop off' at the South Terminal, keeping in the right hand land and head to the far end where a driver will meet you. Emergency number: 07805927969. Please ensure your printed confirmation is placed on your dashboard in full view of any Traffic Wardens.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt;North Terminal: To ensure all our clients have a fast and efficient service, please collect all your luggage, clear customs and when you are in the arrivals hall call 01293 824221 (select option 1) to have your car delivered. There is a no waiting policy at this terminal so please ensure you are ready to collect your car when you call. Exit the building on the ground floor, walk between the 2 cars parks opposite and wait in the far end of the set down area. Emergency number: 07805 927969.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;South Terminal: To ensure all our clients have a fast and efficient service, please collect all your luggage, clear customs and when you are in the arrivals hall call 01293 824221 (select option 1) to have your car delivered. There is a no waiting policy at this terminal so please ensure you are ready to collect your car when you call. Follow signs for 'Courtesy Coaches', exit the building and take a lift down to the ground floor. Cross to the outside lane where your car will be delivered to you. Emergency number: 07805 927969.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Purple Parking Meet &amp;amp; Greet is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 01293 824221&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; EMERGENCY NUMBER: 07805927969&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; FAX: 01293 515767&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located adjacent to the airport and less than 3 miles from the terminals.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park is manned 24 hours a day and has peripheral fencing, lighting, locked gates and CCTV. The car park holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled></facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWR.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGW8</code><airport>LGW</airp