11).&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the 1st roundabout take the 3rd exit signposted A2011 for Horsham.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout with traffic lights take the 4th exit towards Redhill/Gatwick (A23 Northbound)&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Carry on over the next roundabout following the signs for Gatwick.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the next roundabout take the 1st exit for Lowfield Heath/Charlwood.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Turn left at the mini-roundabout onto Charlwood Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Purple Parking is located 1&amp;frac12; miles ahead on the right hand side.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; PLEASE NOTE: You will be required to leave your keys with reception as they will park your car whilst you transfer to the airport. Please also note that some Sat Nav devices aren't accurate enough with just the postcode, so please enter the full address.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; On arrival at Purple Parking, keep to the left hand lane and drive through the automatic barrier. Park in one of the arrival bays and note the lane number. Go to Reception and present them with your booking confirmation or booking reference and car and flight details. Place your keys in the red key box with the corresponding lane number and then take the bus to your terminal. The bus leaves from the Reception area and calls at both terminals. We recommend that you allow 45 minutes from checking into the car park to reaching the airport terminal.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt;Catch the transfer bus from where you were dropped off. You'll need to show the ticket you were given at check-in to the driver.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;If you're at the South Terminal, turn left out of the terminal and wait at bus stop 7 or 8, about 25 yards from the exit.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;If you're at the North Terminal, turn right out of the terminal and follow signs for buses. Wait at bus stop 6 or 7.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;After you've collected your keys from reception, drive to the exit and scan the barcode attached to your keys at the exit barrier to get out.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Airparks Gatwick is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>01293 842901  &lt;br /&gt; FAX: 08700 134653</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; Purple Parking is located 3 miles from the airport terminals.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Purple Parking operate transfers to and from the airport every 20 minutes which take 10 - 15 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>10 - 15 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Airparks Gatwick has CCTV and 24-hour staffing. This car park has been awarded the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>Mini buses, high sided vehicles, mobile homes, lorries, caravans and trailers are not permitted.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>All buses are fully DDA compliant and are suitable for wheelchair use. Assistance with your luggage is available if required from the bus driver.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGW8.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWV</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>SHORT STAY NORTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Convenient Terminal access.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;No minimum stay.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal, Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0PJ&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; From the direction of London or Brighton, exit the M23 at junction 9, following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; Go straight ahead at the first roundabout (J9a) following signs for the North Terminal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; At the next roundabout take the first exit signposted North Terminal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; Move to the left-hand lane and approach the entrance barriers to the short stay car parks, which are directly ahead.&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; On arrival, pull up to the barrier and wait up to 10 seconds for the vehicle registration to be scanned. If the registration is recognised, a ticket will print with the booking reference above the barcode. If not, please press the button for a ticket.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; Follow the road signage to either car park 5 or car park 6. It is recommended that you mark the back of the parking ticket with the car park, level and row, to aid you on your return.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Once you have found your car, please drive up to the exit barriers and insert your ticket which should raise the barrier.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; If you had to press for a ticket on entry, please use the call button and quote your booking reference to the attendant. They will then cross check your booking and open the barrier for exit. &lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 08448 118311&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located at the airport.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Transfers are not required with this service.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>48</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWV.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWU</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>SHORT STAY SOUTH TERMINAL</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Convenient Terminal access.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Simply park your car and take your keys with you.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;No minimum stay.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Convenient Terminal access&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take your keys with you&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;No minimum stay&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay South Terminal, Gatwick Airport, West Sussex, RH6 0LL&lt;/p&gt;</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; From the direction of London or Brighton, exit the M23 at junction 9, following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; Use the filter lane and turn left at the first roundabout (J9a) following signs for the South Terminal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; Continue straight towards the terminal and take the 3rd turning (filter lane) on the right with the South Terminal Short Stay ticket&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; barriers directly ahead.&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; On arrival, pull up to the barrier and wait up to 10 seconds for the vehicle registration to be scanned. If the registration is recognised, a ticket will print with the booking reference above the barcode. If not, please press the button for a ticket and keep the ticket safe as you will require it on exit. Follow the road signs to either multi-storey car park 1 (Blue), 2 (Red) or 3 (Orange). We recommend you mark the back of the parking ticket with the car park, level and row, to aid you on your return.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Once you have found your car, please drive up to the exit barriers and insert your ticket which should raise the barrier.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt; If you had to press for a ticket on entry, please use the call button and quote your booking reference to the attendant. They will then cross check your booking and open the barrier for exit.&lt;/p&gt;</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>&lt;p&gt; Short Stay North Terminal is open 365 days a year.&lt;/p&gt;</openingPeriods><helpline>&lt;p&gt; 08448 118311&lt;/p&gt;</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is located at the airport.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; Transfers are not required with this service.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>&lt;p&gt; The car park is manned 24-hours a day, 365-days a year and frequently patrolled by trained staff. The site has CCTV and security lighting in addition to being an on-site parking facility next to the terminal within the Gatwick airport perimeter.&amp;nbsp;Park Mark 'Safer Parking'&amp;nbsp;approved.&lt;/p&gt;</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>48</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>&lt;p&gt; Blue Badge parking with wide bays and easy access are provided on various levels of both car parks 5 and 6. For your convenience Gatwick suggests using level 3 of car park 5 as this gives direct, same level access to the terminal building. Gatwick car parks are fully compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act (DDA).&amp;nbsp;&lt;a&gt;More about&amp;nbsp;Blue Badge Parking at Gatwick Airport.&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/LGWU.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>LGWN</code><airport>LGW</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>SUMMER SPECIAL PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Secure and convenient on-airport parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Great value parking - ideal for North Terminal departures.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation></furtherInformation><address>Larkins Rd, Gatwick Airport, RH6 0ND</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;br /&gt;From the Direction of London or Brighton:   &lt;li&gt;Exit the M23 at Junction 9 following signs on the roundabout for Gatwick Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Go straight ahead at the first roundabout (J9a) following signs for the North Terminal..&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the North Terminal roundabout take the third exit.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Proceed past the Shell petrol station on the right and go straight over the next small roundabout.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the road to the next roundabout&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn left and then take the first right following the signs to Summer Special Parking.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival, go to Customer Reception. You will be asked to leave your voucher/car keys and you will receive a receipt. Your vehicle will be parked by one of our Valet Staff leaving you free to board the courtesy coach to the terminal.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return follow signs for &amp;quot;Long term car parks&amp;quot;. Coaches for Summer Special are located at the bus stop on the left as you exit the terminal on the lower forecourt. On return to the car park, go to reception with the receipt you were given on entry and exchange for your keys. Your car will be parked in 