&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The car park is located 4 miles away from the Airport &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Security fencing. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The car park has barrier control.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;CCTV &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Park Mark safer Parking Award. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bradnor Road, Sharston Industrial Area, Manchester, M22 4TE</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; Please contact APH on 0161 945 8122 fifteen minutes prior to your arrival at the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Manchester International Airport has its own dedicated exit on the M56 (J5).&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Exit the M56 at Junction 5.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow the cube colour signs to your terminal of departure.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; FOR TERMINAL 1:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow signs for Terminal 1 Departures, go into drop off area at the far end.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; An APH chauffeur wearing an orange jacket and an APH identity badge will meet you at the designated collection point for your terminal.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; FOR TERMINAL 2:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Follow signs for Terminal 2 Departures, go to the far end of the Departure level.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; An APH chauffeur wearing an orange jacket and an APH identity badge will meet you at the designated collection point for your terminal.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; FOR TERMINAL 3:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt; Follow signs T3 Departures, the driver will meet you in the ‘Drop off Area’&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt; An APH chauffeur wearing an orange jacket and an APH identity badge will meet you at the designated collection point for your terminal.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; PLEASE NOTE TERMINALS 1 &amp;amp; 3 HAVE A HEIGHT RESTRICTION OF 2.0 M (6 FT 6INS). If your vehicle exceeds this please call the car park in advance and we will give you an alternative pick up point.&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>&lt;p&gt; Please contact APH on 0161 945 8122 fifteen minutes prior to your arrival at the terminal. An Purple Parking chauffeur wearing an orange jacket and an Purple Parking Identity Badge will meet you at the designated collection point for your terminal. On arrival the chauffeur will check your booking details, mileage and for any vehicle damage, before issuing you with a receipt for your car.&lt;/p&gt;</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full instructions for the returns procedure will be issued to you by the chauffeur on arrival at the terminal.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0161 945 8122  &lt;br /&gt;Fax: 0161 946 1186</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; PURPLE PARKING&amp;nbsp; is located approximately 4 miles from the airport.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park has barrier control, CCTV and holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>There is a vehicle height restriction of 2.0m or 6.5ft for Terminals 1 &amp;amp; 3. If your vehicle exceeds this please call the car park in advance and we will give you an alternative pick up point.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>This service is ideal for disabled travellers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/MANM.jpg</logoURL></carPark><carPark><code>MANE</code><airport>MAN</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>PURPLE PARKING PARK AND RIDE</name><description>&lt;li&gt;BRAND NEW!&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Exclusive.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Only 5 minutes away from the Airport&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Free transfers run 24 hours a day.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Great value for money&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Holds the Park Mark Safer Parking Award. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Service is available for all three terminals. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The car park has barrier control, CCTV&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Service operates 24 hour a day. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Bradnor Road, Sharston Industrial Area,,Manchester, M22 4TE.</address><directions>&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the M60 Anti-Clockwise: Exit at Junction 5 and take the A5103 towards Manchester Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; At the 2nd junction turn left onto the A560.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Carry on over the next roundabout and at the 2nd roundabout turn left onto the B5168, Sharston Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Take the 1st left onto Bradnor Road and PURPLE PARKING/ APH is located on the right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From the M60 Clockwise: Exit at Junction 4 onto the M56.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Exit the M56 at Junction 2 and take the 3rd exit onto the B5168, Sharston Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Take the 1st left onto Bradnor Road and PURPLE PARKING/APH is located on the right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; From Cheshire: Join the M56.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Exit at Junction 3a and turn right onto the A560.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Carry on over the next roundabout and at the 2nd roundabout turn left onto the B5168, Sharston Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; Take the 1st left onto Bradnor Road and PURPLE PARKING/APH is located on the right.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>On arrival at car park report to reception and present your confirmation slip or quote your Booking Reference number.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>Full instructions for the return procedure will be issued on arrival at the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>The car park is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0161 945 8122 Car Park telephone number Vat No. 726 0035 69</helpline><distanceToAirport>&lt;p&gt; PURPLE PARKING is located approximately 4 miles from the airport.&lt;/p&gt;</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>&lt;p&gt; PURPLE PARKING operate transfers to and from the airport every 10 - 15 minutes which take 5 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</transferFromAirport><transferTime>10 minutes</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park has barrier control, CCTV and holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>There is a vehicle height restriction of 2.0m or 6.5ft for Terminals 1 &amp;amp; 3. If your vehicle exceeds this please call the car park in advance and we will give you an alternative pick up point.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>This service is ideal for disabled travellers.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/MANE.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"NCL\"><name>Newcastle International Airport</name><shortname>newcastleinternationalairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>NCLA</code><airport>NCL</airport><serviceType>P</serviceType><name>NEWCASTLE ON AIRPORT PARKING</name><description>&lt;li&gt;On Airport, Safe, Secure &amp;amp; Convenient.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Courtesy shuttle bus available.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Only 300 yards from the terminal.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;The car park has 24-hour CCTV, 24-hour security patrols, entry and exit barriers and a fence.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Official on-airport long stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;</furtherInformation><address>Woolsington, Newcastle Upon Tyne, NE13 8BZ</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;li&gt;From the A1: Follow the A1 to the junction with the A696 at Kenton just outside Newcastle Upon Tyne.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Take the A696 and follow the signs for the airport for 3 miles.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;At the airport follow the signs to the Long Stay Car Park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Take a ticket at the barrier and park in the designated area.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>Take a ticket at the barrier and park in the designated area. Take the courtesy bus to the terminal and take the ticket with you.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>On your return collect your car and take your ticket and booking reference to the Customer Service Office near the exit of the car park.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Airparks is open 365 days a year.</openingPeriods><helpline>0191 214 4341 Car park telephone number. Vat No. 726 0035 69</helpline><distanceToAirport>The car park is situated within the airport's perimeter and is just minutes from the terminal building.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with Newcastle Airport Parking as their Long Stay car park is located close to the Airport terminal. There is also a frequent courtesy bus service to take you and your luggage to the terminal.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>Less than 5 minutes.</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>The car park has a 24hr CCTV monitoring system and holds the 'Park Mark' safer parking award.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize></maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>0</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>The car park has designated extra-wide car spaces,and courtesy buses have a `kneeling` suspension for easy boarding.</facilitiesForDisabled><mapURL></mapURL><errata></errata><logoURL>https://assets.purpleparking.com/products/badges/NCLA.jpg</logoURL></carPark></carParks></airport><airport code=\"NWI\"><name>Norwich Airport</name><shortname>norwichairport</shortname><terminals><terminal>1</terminal></terminals><carParks><carPark><code>NWIA</code><airport>NWI</airport><serviceType>M</serviceType><name>DROP &amp; GO BRONZE SERVICE MEET &amp; GREET</name><description>&lt;li&gt;Convenient chauffeur meet &amp;amp; greet service.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;Includes a car wash, dry and window polish.&lt;/li&gt;</description><furtherInformation>Convenient chauffeur meet &amp;amp; greet service.,Includes a car wash, dry and window polish.</furtherInformation><address>Norwich International Airport, Amsterdam Way, Norwich, NR6 6JA</address><directions>&lt;p&gt;IMPORTANT: Please call 07876 717674 when you are approximately 20 minutes from the airport to confirm your arrival time.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the West: Take the A11 to Norwich.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Turn left onto the A140 and follow the directions below.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the East: Take the A47 to Norwich.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At Postwick take the A1042 Norwich Ring Road.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Carry on along the A1042 until it meets the A140.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Take the A140 North to Norwich Airport and follow the directions below.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt;From the North/South: Take the A140 to Norwich Airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the airport crossroads, turn into Amsterdam Way towards the airport.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;At the 1st roundabout head straight over keeping on Amsterdam Way.&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;Follow the signs to the Short Stay car park.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;/ul&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</directions><arrivalProcedure>Please call 07876 717674 when you are approximately 20 minutes from the airport to confirm your arrival time. On arrival at Norwich Airport, drive to the drop off point in the short stay car park. Please take the ticket issued at the barrier and pass it to your driver. A Drop &amp;amp; Go representative, identified by a board displaying the Drop &amp;amp; Go Logo will be waiting in the drop and pick up area. While you unload your luggage we will check in your car.</arrivalProcedure><departureProcedure>When you have collected your baggage please telephone 07876 717674 to receive details of where your driver will meet you with your vehicle.</departureProcedure><openingPeriods>Drop &amp;amp; Go Parking is open from 04:00 to 23:00 every day.</openingPeriods><helpline>01603 754428</helpline><distanceToAirport>Drop &amp;amp; Go Parking's car park is located about 1 mile from the airport terminal.</distanceToAirport><transferFromAirport>Transfers are not required with this service as your car is collected from you and returned to you at the airport.</transferFromAirport><transferTime>N/A</transferTime><transferFrequency></transferFrequency><cancellations></cancellations><securityMeasures>Drop &amp;amp; Go Parking has a secured storage site that is manned and fully fenced with on-site security patrols.</securityMeasures><maximumCarSize>Drop &amp;amp; Go Parking are unable to accept lorries, vans, mobile homes or caravans.</maximumCarSize><leadTimeHours>48</leadTimeHours><facilitiesForDisabled>This service is ideal for disabled customers. On your return please call 07876 717674 and advise the chauffeur of that you require special assistance. Your car will then be delivered back to you at one of the disabled bays o